SIMPLE: twaddle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twaddle
<hw>Twad"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Twattle</er>.]</ety> <def>To talk in a weak and silly manner, like
one whose faculties are decayed; to prate; to prattle.</def>
<rj><au>Stanyhurst.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twaddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twaddle
<hw>Twad"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Silly talk; gabble;
fustian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have put in this chapter on fighting . . . because of the cant
and <qex>twaddle</qex> that's talked of boxing and fighting with fists
now-a-days.</q> <rj><qau>T. Hughes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twaddler</ent>⟦br⟧
